{
  "texts": [
    "Stratification of stellar Hα activity levels.",
    "The stratification of stellar Hα activity levels refers to the distinct Hα activity properties for different activity levels of solar-like stars.",
    "It can be manifested by the distributions of the Hα activity indices with stellar atmospheric parameters (He et al 2023; He 2024), and by the correlations between the activity indices of different Hydrogen Balmer lines (He 2024).",
    "In this study, the stratification of stellar Hα activity levels is manifested by the distribution of Hα variability (log R EXT Hα) with Hα activity intensity (log R median",
    "As the result obtained in Section 5.1, the distribution of log R EXT Hα of the stellar sources with higher activity levels (log R median Hα > -4.85) is distinctly different from that of the stellar sources with lower activity levels (log R median Hα < -4.85)."
  ]
}